---
import LegalDoc from "@layouts/LegalDoc.astro";
import { COHORT } from "@lib/data/cohort";
---

<LegalDoc
  title="Terms & Conditions · Build Space"
  description="The terms that govern enrolment in the Build Space Logic Labs cohort, including fees, refunds, eligibility, and code ownership."
  heading="Terms & Conditions"
  lastUpdated="10 June 2026"
>
  <p>
    These Terms & Conditions ("Terms") govern your use of
    <a href={COHORT.url}>{COHORT.url}</a> (the "Site") and your enrolment in the
    Build Space Logic Labs cohort (the "Programme"), operated by
    <strong>Build Space</strong> ("Build Space", "we", "us", or "our"). By
    booking the demo class or enrolling, you agree to these Terms.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Who can enrol</h2>
  <p>
    The Programme is designed for students in Class 9 to 12 in India. Because many
    students are under 18, enrolment must be completed by a parent or legal
    guardian, who accepts these Terms on the student's behalf and is responsible
    for payment.
  </p>

  <h2>2. The demo class and the cohort</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Demo class.</strong> The first class costs <strong>₹99</strong>.
      Your child builds something small, meets the instructor, and takes a short
      live assessment. Scholarships, where offered, are decided here on merit.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Full cohort.</strong> The cohort fee is
      <strong>{COHORT.priceDisplay}</strong>, paid once. Where a merit scholarship
      applies, the fee is <strong>{COHORT.scholarshipPriceDisplay}</strong>. The
      Programme runs over {COHORT.durationWeeks} weekends — {COHORT.totalSessions}
      live sessions of {COHORT.sessionHours} hours each.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Fees, payment, and refunds</h2>
  <div class="legal-callout">
    <strong>Both fees are non-refundable.</strong> The ₹99 demo class fee and the
    {COHORT.priceDisplay} cohort fee are non-refundable once paid. We state this
    upfront rather than in fine print.
  </div>
  <p>
    Payments are made over UPI and processed securely by Razorpay. There is no
    EMI option and no hidden charges. If a session is cancelled by us, we will
    reschedule it or provide a recording; this does not create a right to a refund.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Scholarships</h2>
  <p>
    Scholarships are awarded at our discretion, based on a student's performance
    in the demo class and live assessment. A scholarship reduces the cohort fee as
    described at the time it is offered. Scholarships are not transferable and have
    no cash value.
  </p>

  <h2>5. What we provide</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>{COHORT.totalSessions} live online sessions, {COHORT.sessionHours} hours each.</li>
    <li>One instructor across the whole cohort.</li>
    <li>Session recordings if a class is missed.</li>
    <li>Support for questions between sessions, via the channels we provide.</li>
    <li>A completion certificate and parent observer access to sessions.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Sessions run online over Chrome or Safari. You are responsible for a working
    internet connection and a suitable device.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Ownership of student work</h2>
  <p>
    Code and projects your child writes during the Programme belong to your child.
    They keep their GitHub repository and any agent they deploy. We may, with your
    consent, showcase student work (for example on a demo day or in marketing); we
    will ask before doing so.
  </p>
  <p>
    The Programme's teaching materials, curriculum, and Site content are owned by
    Build Space and may not be copied, resold, or redistributed without our
    written permission.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>You agree not to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Share class join links, recordings, or materials with people outside your enrolment.</li>
    <li>Disrupt sessions or behave abusively toward the instructor or other students.</li>
    <li>Use the Site or Programme for any unlawful purpose.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We may remove a participant who breaches these Terms, without a refund.
  </p>

  <h2>8. No guarantee of outcomes</h2>
  <p>
    We teach the principles behind building AI agents and help every student ship
    a working project. We cannot, however, guarantee any particular academic,
    admission, or career outcome, as those depend on many factors outside our
    control.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the extent permitted by law, Build Space is not liable for any
    indirect or consequential loss arising from the use of the Site or the
    Programme. Our total liability for any claim is limited to the amount you paid
    us for the Programme.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Changes to these Terms</h2>
  <p>
    We may update these Terms from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the
    top shows the current version. Continued use of the Site or Programme after a
    change means you accept the updated Terms.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Governing law</h2>
  <p>
    These Terms are governed by the laws of India. Any dispute is subject to the
    exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of India.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Contact us</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Email: <a href={`mailto:${COHORT.contact.email}`}>{COHORT.contact.email}</a></li>
    <li>WhatsApp: {COHORT.contact.whatsapp}</li>
    <li>Build Space, India.</li>
  </ul>
</LegalDoc>
